# Privacy Policy

**Last Updated: February 1, 2026**

## Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how Photo Grid ("we," "our," "us," or "Company") collects, uses, discloses, and safeguards your information when you use our application (the "App") that integrates with Meta's services to pull and display Instagram posts.

We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring you have a positive experience on our App. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our App.

---

## 1. Information We Collect

### 1.1 Information You Provide Directly

- **Account Credentials**: When you authorize our App through Meta's login, we collect your Meta/Facebook account information necessary to authenticate access
- **Profile Information**: Your Instagram business account profile data including username, bio, profile picture, and account type
- **Instagram Post Data**: Content from Instagram posts including captions, images, videos, timestamps, engagement metrics (likes, comments, shares), and hashtags
- **Preferences and Settings**: Your preferences regarding how you want to use the App (e.g., which posts to pull, frequency of updates)

### 1.2 Information Collected Automatically

- **Device Information**: Device type, operating system, device identifiers, and mobile network information
- **Usage Data**: Information about how you interact with the App, including features accessed, actions taken, and time spent
- **Location Data**: General location information derived from device settings (if enabled)
- **Log Data**: IP address, browser type, pages visited, and timestamps
- **Cookies and Similar Technologies**: We use cookies, web beacons, and similar tracking technologies to recognize you and improve your experience

### 1.3 Information from Meta/Instagram

Through Meta's Graph API and Instagram's API, we receive:
- Instagram business account information
- Post content and metadata
- Audience insights (if available through your permissions)
- Business account performance metrics
- Follower and engagement data accessible through your Instagram business account

---

## 2. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

- **Service Provision**: To authenticate your account, retrieve your Instagram posts, and display them within our App
- **App Functionality**: To pull, organize, store, and manage your Instagram content according to your preferences
- **Analytics and Improvement**: To understand how the App is used and to improve features, performance, and user experience
- **Communication**: To send you service-related notifications, updates, and support messages
- **Security**: To detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and unauthorized access
- **Compliance**: To comply with legal obligations and Meta's Terms of Service
- **Marketing**: To send promotional materials and updates about our services (you can opt out)

---

## 3. How We Share Your Information

### 3.1 No Third-Party Selling

We do not sell your personal information to third parties.

### 3.2 Service Providers

We share information with third-party vendors who perform services on our behalf, including:
- Cloud hosting providers
- Analytics providers
- Customer support platforms
- Payment processors (if applicable)

These service providers are contractually obligated to use your information only as necessary to provide services to us.

### 3.3 Meta/Meta Platforms

Our App functions through Meta's APIs and Graph API. Your use of our App inherently involves sharing data with Meta. Meta's privacy policy governs their use of data. By using our App, you acknowledge that Meta may collect data about your use of Instagram's services.

### 3.4 Legal Requirements

We may disclose your information when required by law or when we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to:
- Comply with legal obligations, court orders, or government requests
- Protect and defend our legal rights
- Prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing
- Protect the personal safety of users or the public

### 3.5 Business Transfers

If our Company is involved in a merger, acquisition, bankruptcy, dissolution, or similar transaction or proceeding, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.

---

## 4. Data Security

We implement appropriate technical, administrative, and physical safeguards to protect your information, including:

- Encryption of data in transit using HTTPS/TLS
- Secure authentication mechanisms
- Access controls and role-based permissions
- Regular security assessments
- Secure storage of API credentials and access tokens

However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security of your information.

---

## 5. Data Retention

We retain your information for as long as necessary to provide our services and fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. Specifically:

- **Account Data**: Retained while your account is active and for 30 days after deletion
- **Instagram Posts**: Retained according to your settings (you can request deletion at any time)
- **Usage Data**: Generally retained for 12 months
- **Log Data**: Retained for up to 90 days

You may request deletion of your data at any time by contacting us. Some data may be retained to comply with legal obligations.

---

## 6. Your Rights and Choices

### 6.1 Access and Portability

You have the right to access the personal information we hold about you and, in some jurisdictions, to receive a copy in a portable format.

### 6.2 Correction and Deletion

You have the right to request correction of inaccurate data and deletion of your information, subject to certain exceptions.

### 6.3 Opt-Out

You can opt out of:
- Marketing communications by clicking "unsubscribe" or adjusting notification settings
- Certain analytics tracking (though this may limit functionality)
- Cookies through your browser settings

### 6.4 Withdraw Consent

You may withdraw consent for the App to access your Instagram account at any time by:
- Revoking the App's permissions in your Instagram settings
- Contacting us directly
- Deleting the App

Withdrawal of consent will not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before withdrawal.

### 6.5 Do Not Track

Some browsers include a "Do Not Track" feature. Our App does not currently respond to Do Not Track signals.

---

## 7. Meta/Instagram API Compliance

Our App uses Meta's Graph API and Instagram APIs in compliance with Meta's Platform Policy, Instagram Brand Guidelines, and API Terms. Specifically:

- We only access data that you explicitly authorize
- We do not store or cache Instagram posts longer than necessary
- We do not scrape or extract data beyond API terms
- We respect Instagram's platform policies regarding data usage
- We do not use data for surveillance, targeting discrimination, or other prohibited purposes

You can revoke the App's access to your Instagram account at any time through your Instagram settings.

---

## 8. Children's Privacy

Our App is not intended for children under 13 years old. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn we have collected such information, we will delete it promptly. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us immediately.

---

## 9. International Data Transfers

If you are located outside the United States, be aware that your information may be transferred to, stored in, and processed in the United States and other countries where our service providers are located. These countries may have data protection laws that differ from your home country. By using our App, you consent to the transfer of your information to countries outside your country of residence.

---

## 10. California Privacy Rights (CCPA)

If you are a California resident, you have the following rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act:

- **Right to Know**: You can request what personal information we collect, use, and disclose
- **Right to Delete**: You can request deletion of personal information we have collected
- **Right to Opt-Out**: You can opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information
- **Right to Non-Discrimination**: We will not discriminate against you for exercising your rights

To exercise these rights, contact us using the information below.

---

## 11. GDPR Compliance (EU Residents)

If you are located in the European Union, you have the following rights:

- **Right of Access**: Access to your personal data
- **Right to Rectification**: Correction of inaccurate data
- **Right to Erasure**: Deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten")
- **Right to Restrict Processing**: Limit how we use your data
- **Right to Data Portability**: Receive your data in a structured format
- **Right to Object**: Object to processing of your data
- **Right to Lodge a Complaint**: File a complaint with your local data protection authority

Our legal basis for processing your data includes your consent, performance of our service, and our legitimate interests.

---

## 12. Third-Party Links

Our App may contain links to third-party websites and applications. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing personal information.

---

## 13. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements, or other factors. We will notify you of material changes by posting the updated policy in the App and updating the "Last Updated" date. Your continued use of the App after changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.

---

